snippet.title: Measurement - Area Of A Garden - Multiplying a Constant By Binomial
snippet.description:
http://tapintoteenminds.com Using area models to multiply a binomial by a constant with distributive property. This is a contextual math problem that may be considered contrived, but really gives a visual in regards to distribution when a single variable term is involved.

Great for making math contextual, visual and interconnected.
